The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Academy meet

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: India are not participating in a academy tri-series that is now being played in Bangladesh. The academy teams of Sri Lanka, Pakistan and Bangladesh are involved in the meet that concludes on Monday. 

Explaining Indias non-participation, joint secretary M.P. Pandove said: In keeping with the BCCIs policy, we dont send our academy team for participation in tournaments abroad. The players are generally part of the India U-17, U-19 or A tours. 




